From 01058975992154514df25bc40382d5875ade1758 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miro Mraz <mraz.miro@seznam.cz>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 01:37:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Input: stmfts - extend post-reset delay to allow FTM5
 firmware boot

The previous 50 ms wait after deasserting reset is sufficient for FTS4
chips but too short for FTM5 (FTM5CU56AA1BE on Pixel 4a, chip ID 0x4836).
The FTM5 bootloader runs internal CRC verification of code+config flash
sections before it transitions to app mode and begins ACKing I2C reads.
On the tested hardware this consistently takes ~300 ms; 500 ms gives
comfortable headroom.

Symptom before this fix: probe failed with -ENXIO inside stmfts5_configure
when i2c_smbus_read_i2c_block_data(0x86) was issued ~70 ms after reset
deassert, before the chip's I2C state machine was up. ftrace
function_graph with funcgraph-retval pinpointed the failing I2C
transaction; dmesg showed only the dev_dbg 'initializing...' line.

A future patch should replace the fixed sleep with a poll-until-ready
loop reading STMFTS_READ_ALL_EVENT, which is the actual chip-level
readiness signal.

Signed-off-by: Miro Mraz <mraz.miro@seznam.cz>
---
 drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c
index e613299e3..149c45c53 100644
--- a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c
+++ b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stmfts.c
@@ -834,7 +834,7 @@ static void stmfts_reset(struct stmfts_data *sdata)
 	msleep(20);
 
 	gpiod_set_value_cansleep(sdata->reset_gpio, 0);
-	msleep(50);
+	msleep(500); /* FTM5 fw boot takes >300ms before chip ACKs I2C */
 }
 
 static int stmfts_configure(struct stmfts_data *sdata)
